{% comment %}
  sections/homepage-hero.liquid
  ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  Jedi homepage hero section.

  Rendered after the path-chooser entry screen fades out.
  Only styled when body[data-gf-side="light"] is present — set by path-chooser.js
  after the visitor chooses Light Side.

  Structure:
    <section>               ← the full hero block (70vh)
      <div> inner           ← centers content, caps max-width
        <p>  eyebrow        ← small uppercase label above the headline
        <h1> title          ← main headline
        <p>  sub            ← supporting sentence
        <a>  button         ← CTA link to the Light Side collection
  ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
{% endcomment %}

{% comment %} Load this section's stylesheet {% endcomment %}
{{ 'homepage-hero.css' | asset_url | stylesheet_tag }}

<section class="gf-hero" aria-label="Hero">

  <div class="gf-hero__inner">

    {% comment %}
      Eyebrow — small label above the headline.
      This signals what type of page/section this is before the visitor reads the headline.
    {% endcomment %}
    <p class="gf-hero__eyebrow">Light Side Artifacts</p>

    {% comment %}
      Headline — the hero's main statement.
      h1 because this is the most important heading on the page.
    {% endcomment %}
    <h1 class="gf-hero__title">Forge Your <span class="gf-hero__accent">Legend</span></h1>

    {% comment %}
      Subtext — one sentence that supports the headline.
      Keeps it brief — the headline does the heavy lifting.
    {% endcomment %}
    <p class="gf-hero__sub">
      The galaxy's finest relics, forged for those who stand for peace and the Force.
    </p>

    {% comment %}
      CTA Button — links to the Light Side collection.
      Using an <a> tag (not <button>) because it navigates to a new page.
    {% endcomment %}
    <a href="/collections/light-side" class="gf-hero__btn">
      Shop the Collection
    </a>

  </div>

</section>
